 {"id":"bd-mblr.7.6.2","title":"Deterministic bisect orchestrator","description":"Implement orchestrator that replays failure across commit range and identifies first bad change deterministically.","design":"Implement deterministic bisect orchestrator that executes replay manifests across commit ranges with robust retry and caching logic.","acceptance_criteria":"- Orchestrator supports binary search style commit selection with resumable state.
- Execution logs include commit hash, evaluator result, runtime, and artifact pointers for each step.
- Integration tests validate correctness on synthetic histories with injected flaky and deterministic failures.","notes":"When flakiness is detected, mark result uncertain and escalate instead of fabricating deterministic verdicts.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T03:05:21.611519286Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T03:08:38.186252437Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.7.6.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.7.6","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T03:05:21.611519286Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.7.6.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.7.6.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T03:05:57.809737583Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-mblr.7.6.3","title":"CI and operator hooks for auto-bisect","description":"Add trigger policy for automatic bisect on recurrent failures and publish result artifacts for engineers.","design":"Wire auto bisect triggers into CI and provide operator controls for scope, priority, cancellation, and result publication.","acceptance_criteria":"- CI trigger policy routes eligible regressions into bisect with bounded concurrency controls.
- Result summaries include likely culprit commit range, confidence level, and linked replay artifacts.
- E2e workflow tests cover success, uncertainty, cancellation, and timeout paths.","notes":"Expose manual override commands so maintainers can force rerun with updated manifests when needed.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T03:05:21.697393069Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T03:08:38.266797843Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.7.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.3.2.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T03:05:57.962867502Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.7.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.7.6","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T03:05:21.697393069Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.7.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.7.6.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T03:05:57.886904905Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-mblr.7.7","title":"Resource Leak Budgets and Gates","description":"Add leak observability and budget enforcement for fds/memory/tempfiles/side artifacts across unit and e2e lanes.","design":"Introduce resource telemetry, leak budgets, and gating so long run quality remains stable and regressions are caught before user impact.","acceptance_criteria":"- Resource telemetry covers memory, file descriptors, threads, and temp storage growth across test lanes.
- Leak budgets define threshold policies with severity levels and ownership mapping.
- CI gates enforce budgets with actionable diagnostics instead of opaque failure messages.","notes":"Budgets should scale by workload class to avoid false alarms while preserving strict regression detection.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T03:05:21.775125760Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T03:09:00.646516807Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.7.7","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.7","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T03:05:21.775125760Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
